OL,3,CPost Office confirms 115 branches to
OL,4,Cclose, with 1,000 workers at risk
OL,6,FThe group said it plans to offload 115
OL,7,Fdirectly owned branches within its
OL,8,F11,500 network, which could see them
OL,9,Ftransferred to retail partners or
OL,10,Fpostmasters, or potentially closed.
OL,11,FThey are the only remaining branches
OL,12,Fdirectly owned by the Post Office,
OL,13,Fdown from close to 400 in 2010.
OL,15,FThe branches employ around 1,000
OL,16,Fworkers whose jobs could now be at
OL,17,Frisk. Hundreds of jobs are also under
OL,18,Fthreat at the Post Office's
OL,19,Fheadquarters.
