OL,6,F"We can, and will, restore pride in
OL,7,Fworking for a business with a legacy
OL,8,Fof service, rather than one of
OL,9,Fscandal."
OL,11,FBut the Communication Workers Union
OL,12,F(CWU) union called on the Post Office
OL,13,Fto halt the plans and for the
OL,14,Fgovernment to intervene.
OL,16,FCWU general secretary Dave Ward said:
OL,17,F"For the company to announce the
OL,18,Fclosure of hundreds of Post Offices
OL,19,Fhot on the heels of the Horizon
OL,20,Fscandal is as tone deaf as it is
OL,21,Fimmoral.
